## Feature: EVA Brain v2 AI Assistant [ID=F46-03]

Wire the EVA Brain v2 FastAPI backend (port 8001) as the AI Assistant chat panel.

### Story: Implement brain-client.ts typed API client [ID=F46-03-001]

Create `src/lib/brain-client.ts`:
- `chatUngrounded(query, history?, actorOid?)` ŌĆö POST /v1/chat/ungrounded
- `chatGrounded(query, history?, indexes?, actorOid?)` ŌĆö POST /v1/chat
- `pingBrain()` ŌĆö GET /v1/health ŌåÆ boolean
- All calls include 4 mandatory headers: `X-Actor-OID`, `X-Correlation-ID`, `X-Caller-App: accelerator`, `X-Environment`
- `BRAIN_BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_BRAIN_BASE_URL ?? '/api/brain'`

Accept: TypeScript compiles; `pingBrain()` resolves true when Brain v2 is running.

### Story: Add /api/brain Vite proxy [ID=F46-03-002]

Add `server.proxy['/api/brain']` in `vite.config.ts` ŌåÆ `http://localhost:8001` with path rewrite stripping `/api/brain`.
Accept: `npm run dev` proxies `/api/brain/v1/health` to Brain v2 in dev.

### Story: Build AIAssistant chat panel component [ID=F46-03-003]

Create `src/components/AIAssistant.tsx`:
- `pingBrain()` on mount ŌåÆ `brainOnline` state ŌåÆ `EvaBadge` (Brain Online / Brain Offline)
- Offline: warning banner + disabled `Textarea`
- Conversation history state passed on every `chatUngrounded()` call
- 5 starter suggestion chips when conversation is empty
- Error messages rendered in distinct error bubble
- Uses `EvaButton`, `EvaSpinner`, `EvaBadge` from `@eva/ui`

Accept: Panel renders in `assistant` view; badge reflects brain health; messages round-trip.

### Story: Add AI Assistant view to App.tsx [ID=F46-03-004]

Add `View = 'assistant'` type. Add `SparkleRegular` nav tab. Render `<AIAssistant />` on view switch.
Accept: AI Assistant tab visible; click navigates to panel.

